    {
      "id": "tchO",
      "code_hash": "fcbd39c8ed33763cda0b369441a5fdf7",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">You build a tree. The renderer asks the tree what it is, the profile what the rules are, and the formatter what it should look like. Three jobs, three places.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">A tag is data. <code>El(\"div\", {...}, (...))</code> holds a name, attrs, and children \u2014 nothing more. <code>Txt</code> and <code>Raw</code> are leaves. <code>Frag</code> is a tuple of siblings with no wrapper.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Authoring builds that tree. <code>mk_tag(\"div\")</code> returns a constructor; calling it makes an <code>El</code>; calling the <code>El</code> again extends it. <code>cls=</code> becomes <code>class=</code>, <code>None</code> and <code>False</code> drop out, strings become <code>Txt</code>. The tree is the only thing your components return.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The profile is a table. It lists which names are void, which are raw, which switch namespace. HTML5 is one table; SVG sits inside it as a switch rule. Want a different dialect? Pass a different table.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The walk turns the tree into events: <code>open</code>, <code>close</code>, <code>void</code>, <code>txt</code>, <code>raw</code>. It consults the profile, tracks the namespace, flattens fragments. It does not format.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The formatter turns events into a string. Indent, escape, join. It does not know about HTML.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">To change look, edit the formatter. To change dialect, edit the profile. To change shape, edit the tree. Each change stays in its own room.</span>\n<div class=\"language-scdoc codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>   author code              data                 rules\n  \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510    \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510    \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n  \u2502  mk_tag,     \u2502\u2500\u2500\u2500\u25b6\u2502 El, Txt, Raw \u2502    \u2502   HTML5      \u2502\n  \u2502  tag, frag,  \u2502    \u2502   Frag       \u2502    \u2502   profile    \u2502\n  \u2502  components  \u2502    \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518    \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n  \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518           \u2502                   \u2502\n                             \u25bc                   \u2502\n                      \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510           \u2502\n                      \u2502    walk      \u2502\u25c0\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n                      \u2502  tree\u2192events \u2502\n                      \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n                             \u2502  open / close / void / txt / raw\n                             \u25bc\n                      \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n                      \u2502     fmt      \u2502\n                      \u2502 events\u2192string\u2502\n                      \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n                             \u25bc\n                          HTML out\n</code></pre></div></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "mYYS",
      "code_hash": "6825786617bd4075618b28fe549a7bea",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">A roadmap, smallest-meaningful-step first. Each item should be runnable and checkable on its own.</span>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Node types</strong> \u2014 <code>El</code>, <code>Txt</code>, <code>Raw</code>, <code>Frag</code>. Build a couple by hand, eyeball the repr.</li>\n<li><strong>Authoring helpers</strong> \u2014 <code>_flat</code>, <code>_kid</code>, <code>_kids</code>, <code>_attrs</code>, <code>ATTR_MAP</code>, <code>tag</code>, <code>frag</code>, <code>mk_tag</code>, <code>El.__call__</code>. Check that <code>div(cls='x')(p('hi'))</code> builds the expected tree.</li>\n<li><strong>HTML5 profile</strong> \u2014 the data table only. No code consumes it yet; just print it and confirm it's the shape you want.</li>\n<li><strong>Walk</strong> \u2014 tree \u2192 event stream. Test on a flat doc, a nested doc, a fragment, a void element, an SVG subtree. Confirm namespace switching shows up in the events.</li>\n<li><strong>Format</strong> \u2014 events \u2192 string, with the indentation behaviour you want for SSE / brotli. Test against the same fixtures as step 4.</li>\n<li><strong><code>render</code></strong> \u2014 one-line composition of walk + fmt. This is the public entry point.</li>\n<li><strong>Whitespace cases</strong> \u2014 text-only elements on one line, <code>&lt;pre&gt;</code> preserve, inline elements no break. Add the profile flags, extend <code>fmt</code>, regression-test against step 5.</li>\n<li><strong>Module <code>__getattr__</code> + cache</strong> \u2014 auto-tags by import, stash on the module so repeat lookups are free.</li>\n<li><strong><code>html_doc</code> and <code>Layout</code></strong> \u2014 rebuild as thin wrappers returning <code>Frag</code> / <code>El</code>. Confirm no double-<code>&lt;body&gt;</code>.</li>\n<li><strong><code>html_to_tag</code></strong> \u2014 pick a parser that preserves case so SVG round-trips. Decide whether to keep <code>HTMLParser</code> for HTML and add a separate XML path, or switch wholesale.</li>\n<li><strong>Cdn helpers</strong> \u2014 <code>Datastar</code>, <code>MeCSS</code>, <code>Pointer</code>, <code>Highlight</code>, <code>Color_type_css</code>, <code>Favicon</code>. Mechanical port.</li>\n<li><strong><code>Show</code></strong> \u2014 port the iframe wrapper on top of the new <code>render</code>.</li>\n<li><strong>Context-aware escaping</strong> \u2014 pass <code>escape_for(ctx)</code> into <code>fmt</code>, branch on body / attr / url / js / css. Bolt-on, doesn't touch the tree.</li>\n<li><strong>Regression suite</strong> \u2014 the five-failure cell from earlier becomes the test fixture. Add fragment, multi-root parse, <code>&lt;pre&gt;</code>, inline mixing, SVG case.</li>\n</ol>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Want to start at step 1?</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
